packageMeta.name: purescript-dom
packageMeta.description: PureScript type definitions and effect for interacting with the DOM

declarations.comments:
Effect type for when the DOM is being manipulated or mutable values are
being read from the DOM.
declarations.title: DOM

declarations.comments: Basic type for all DOM events.
declarations.title: Event

declarations.comments: Indicates whether the event will bubble up through the DOM or not.
declarations.title: bubbles

declarations.comments: Indicates whether the event can be cancelled.
declarations.title: cancelable

declarations.comments: The element that the event listener was added to.
declarations.title: currentTarget

declarations.comments: Indicates whether `preventDefault` was called on the event.
declarations.title: defaultPrevented

declarations.comments:
Indicates which phase of the event flow that is currently being processed
for the event.
declarations.title: eventPhase

declarations.comments: The integer value for the current event phase.
declarations.title: eventPhaseIndex

declarations.comments: Cancels the event if it can be cancelled.
declarations.title: preventDefault

declarations.comments:
Prevents all other listeners for the event from being called. This includes
event listeners added to the current target after the current listener.
declarations.title: stopImmediatePropagation

declarations.comments:
Prevents the event from bubbling up to futher event listeners. Other event
listeners on the current target will still fire.
declarations.title: stopPropagation

declarations.comments: The element that was the source of the event.
declarations.title: target

declarations.comments:
The time in milliseconds between 01/01/1970 and when the event was
dispatched.
declarations.title: timeStamp

declarations.comments: The event type.
declarations.title: type_

declarations.comments:
A boxed function that can be used as an event listener. This is necessary
due to the underlying implementation of Eff functions.
declarations.title: EventListener

declarations.comments: Creates an EventListener from a normal PureScript Eff function.
declarations.title: eventListener

declarations.comments:
Adds a listener to an event target. The boolean argument indicates whether
the listener should be added for the "capture" phase.
declarations.title: addEventListener

declarations.comments:
Removes a listener to an event target. The boolean argument indicates
whether the listener should be removed for the "capture" phase.
declarations.title: removeEventListener

declarations.comments: Dispatches an event from an event target.
declarations.title: dispatchEvent

modules.name: DOM.Event.KeyboardEvent
modules.comments:
Functions that expose the KeyboardEvent API.

https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/KeyboardEvent

Note: The deprecated attributes `.keyCode`, `.charCode`, and
`.which` are deliberately omitted. It is currently recommended to use
`KeyboardEvent.key` instead.

If browser support for `KeyboardEvent.key` is not yet widespread
enough for your use case, consider using a polyfill
(e.g. https://github.com/inexorabletash/polyfill#keyboard-events)
or use the purescript FFI to access the deprecated attributes you
want to work with.

declarations.comments:
A non-empty Unicode character string containing the printable representation
of the key, if available.
declarations.title: key

declarations.comments:
Returns a string representing a physical key on the keyboard. Not
affected by keyboard layout or state of the modifier keys.
declarations.title: code

declarations.comments: Basic type for all DOM events.
declarations.title: Event

declarations.comments: The type of strings used for event types.
declarations.title: EventType

declarations.comments: A DOM item that can emit events.
declarations.title: EventTarget

declarations.comments:
`MediaType` of the data contained in the `Blob`.
Returns `Nothing` if the `MediaType` is unknown.
declarations.title: type_

declarations.comments: The size (in bytes) of the data contained in the `Blob`.
declarations.title: size

declarations.comments:
An index into the Blob indicating the first byte to include in the new Blob.
If you specify a negative value, it's treated as an offset from the end of the
string toward the beginning. For example, -10 would be the 10th from last byte
in the Blob. If you specify a value for start that is larger than the size
of the source Blob, the returned Blob has size 0 and contains no data.
declarations.title: StartByte

declarations.comments:
An index into the Blob indicating the first byte that will *not* be included
in the new Blob (i.e. the byte exactly at this index is not included).
If you specify a negative value, it's treated as an offset from the end of
the string toward the beginning. For example, -10 would be the 10th from
last byte in the Blob. The default value is size.
declarations.title: EndByte

declarations.title: idxFromInt

declarations.comments: Creates `ByteIdx` from `Number` value using `Math.round`.
declarations.title: idxFromNumber
